Add the hello-world CTest source files under testsuite/ctest using the correct custom debug-channel structure: a test-local debug header sets DEBUGCHANNELS to a hello-world test namespace and declares extern dc::hello, a separate translation unit defines channel_ct hello("HELLO"), and the test executable captures libcw_do output, reads rcfiles, lists channels, emits Dout(dc::hello, "Hello World!"), and compares the captured output exactly to the expected channel list and hello line.
